object.script:
integral = 0 pvOld = 0 out = 0
function onTick() setpoint = input.getNumber(1) pv = input.getNumber(2) P = input.getNumber(3) I = input.getNumber(4) D = input.getNumber(5)
on = input.getBool(1)
if on then error = setpoint - pv diff = pv - pvOld
if out < 1 and out > 0 then integral = integral + I*error integral = math.max(math.min(integral, 1), 0) end
Kp = P*error Ki = integral Kd = -D*diff
out = Kp+Ki+Kd out = math.max(math.min(out, 1), 0)
else integral = 0 out = 0 end
pvOld = pv
output.setNumber(1, out) end

object.script:
-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() myX = input.getNumber(5) -- Read the first number from the script's composite input myY = input.getNumber(6) myZ = input.getNumber(7) myHeading = input.getNumber(8)
camX = input.getNumber(21) camY = input.getNumber(22) camZ = input.getNumber(23) laser= input.getNumber(24) -- setAlt = input.getNumber(9) MapOff= input.getBool(7)
end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen
function onDraw()
if not MapOff then alpha = 100 screen.setMapColorOcean(0, 0, 50, alpha) screen.setMapColorShallows(50, 50, 100, alpha) screen.setMapColorLand(100, 100, 100, alpha) screen.setMapColorGrass(50, 100, 50, alpha) screen.setMapColorSand(100, 100, 50, alpha) screen.setMapColorSnow(100, 100, 100, alpha)
screen.drawMap(myX, myY, 1) end w = screen.getWidth() -- Get the screen's width and height h = screen.getHeight()
screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) -- screen.drawText(5,1,"Set Alt"..math.floor(setAlt)) screen.drawText(5,1, "Cam X:"..math.floor(camX)) screen.drawText(5,7, "Cam Y:"..math.floor(camY)) screen.drawText(5,13,"Cam Z:"..math.floor(camZ)) screen.drawText(5,19,"Laser:"..math.floor(laser).."m")
screen.setColor(0, 255, 255,150) screen.drawCircle(w / 2-0.5, h / 2-0.5, 2) -- Draw a 30px radius circle in the center of the screen end
